{"title": "US appeals court rules against broad enforcement of travel ban", "url": "http://nypost.com/2017/09/07/us-appeals-court-rules-against-broad-enforcement-of-travel-ban/", "text": "see also Blocked immigrants in travel ban can reapply for visas: DOJ The first lawsuit challenging President Trump\u2019s original travel ban has...\n\nA US appeals court Thursday ruled against President Donald Trump\u2019s effort to broadly enforce a temporary travel and refugee ban on people from certain Muslim-majority countries that the Republican president said was necessary for national security.\n\nA three-judge 9th US Circuit Court of Appeals panel said the government did not persuasively explain why the travel ban should be enforced against grandparents, grandchildren, aunts, uncles, nieces, nephews and cousins from the six countries.\n\nIn the latest legal back-and-forth over the president\u2019s controversial executive order, the court also said refugee resettlement agencies have a \u201cbona fide\u201d relationship with refugees, which under a standard set by the US Supreme Court should allow them into the United States.", "source": "New York Post", "publish_date": "2017-09-07", "type": "article"}